: "(4,457,204)", "bbox": [945.5, 949.6, 1042.7, 970.5]}, {"text": "Total net assets acquired . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .", "bbox": [202.2, 983.0, 903.8, 1003.9]}, {"text": "$ 1,505,091", "bbox": [935.1, 983.0, 1035.8, 1003.8]}, {"text": "(a)", "bbox": [160.5, 1033.2, 182.4, 1052.0]}, {"text": "Reflects the portion of the fair value of the awards attributable to pre-merger employee service. The remaining fair value", "bbox": [198.0, 1033.2, 1119.2, 1052.0]}, {"text": "of the awards will be recognized in Pulte’s operating results over the applicable periods.", "bbox": [198.0, 1056.2, 867.0, 1074.9]}, {"text": "(b)", "bbox": [160.5, 1092.3, 182.4, 1111.1]}, {"text": "Goodwill resulting from the Centex merger is not deductible for federal income tax purposes, though as of the merger", "bbox": [198.0, 1092.3, 1119.2, 1111.1]}, {"text": "date Centex had approximately $39 million of goodwill deductible for tax purposes related to prior acquisitions.", "bbox": [198.0, 1115.2, 1043.1, 1134.0]}, {"text": "Cash and equivalents, other assets, accounts payable, and accrued and other liabilities were generally stated", "bbox": [202.2, 1151.9, 1119.1, 1172.7]}, {"text": "at historical carrying values given the short-term nature of these assets and liabilities. Because Centex had elected", "bbox": [160.5, 1176.9, 1119.0, 1197.7]}, {"text": "the fair value option under ASC 825 for its residential mortgage loans available-for-sale, the historical carrying", "bbox": [160.5, 1201.9, 1119.0, 1222.7]}, {"text": "value of such assets equaled their fair value. Income tax receivables and liabilities were recorded at historical", "bbox": [160.5, 1226.9, 1118.9, 1247.7]}, {"text": "carrying values in accordance with the ASC 805. The fair value of assumed senior notes was determined based on", "bbox": [160.5, 1251.9, 1119.2, 1272.8]}, {"text": "quoted market prices.", "bbox": [160.5, 1276.9, 340.7, 1297.8]}, {"text": "The Company determined the fair value of inventory on a community-by-community basis primarily using a", "bbox": [202.2, 1315.2, 1119.2, 1336.0]}, {"text": "combination of market comparable land transactions, where available, and discounted cash flow models, though", "bbox": [160.5, 1340.2, 1119.2, 1361.0]}, {"text": "independent appraisals were also utilized in certain instances. These estimated cash flows are significantly", "bbox": [160.5, 1365.2, 1118.9, 1386.0]}, {"text": "impacted by estimates related to expected average selling prices and sales incentives, expected sales paces and", "bbox": [160.5, 1390.2, 1119.2, 1411.0]}, {"text": "cancellation rates, expected land development and construction timelines, and anticipated land development,", "bbox": [160.5, 1415.2, 1119.0, 1436.0]}, {"text": "construction, and overhead costs. Such estimates must be made for each individual community and may vary", "bbox": [160.5, 1440.2, 1119.1, 1461.0]}, {"text": "significantly between communities. See Note 5 for additional discussion of the factors impacting the fair value of", "bbox": [160.5, 1465.2, 1119.2, 1486.1]}, {"text": "land inventory.", "bbox": [160.5, 1490.2, 286.7, 1511.1]}, {"text": "63", "bbox": [608.6, 1540.8, 629.4, 1561.6]}]}